  m_Name: Table Manners
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::CodexEntry
  title: Table Manners
  description: 'Formal dining in wealthy households followed strict etiquette rules
    that dictated how tables were set and how guests were expected to behave. The
    placement of cutlery, glassware, and serving dishes was highly structured, often
    reflecting social rank and order. Proper table etiquette was an important part
    of upper-class identity. '
  illustration: {fileID: 21300000, guid: e19fa67114db40d42b9d5fd229b34176, type: 3}
